#!/usr/bin/env python
"""
CESMLC V6 - Problem-state weak/semi-supervised ML trainer
==========================================================

Purpose
-------
Train and evaluate a real multiclass problem-state model from the V6 seed-label
training dataset produced by `cesmlc_v6_seed_label_dataset_builder.py`.

Design
------
- Seed labels are high-precision weak labels, not treated as perfect truth.
- Manual labels, if provided, override seed labels and receive higher weight.
- The model is trained on problem-state feature engineering, not on the final
  seed-label column itself.
- By default, direct seed-rule indicator columns are excluded from the ML feature
  set to avoid simply memorizing the seed-rule decision tree.
- Optional pseudo-labeling can add high-confidence predictions from hold/unlabeled
  rows and retrain, giving a semi-supervised workflow.

Supported backends
------------------
--model auto       : CatBoost -> LightGBM -> sklearn RandomForest fallback
--model catboost   : CatBoost multiclass classifier
--model lightgbm   : LightGBM multiclass classifier
--model sklearn_rf : sklearn RandomForest fallback
--model tabnet     : optional pytorch-tabnet backend

Install examples
----------------
python -m pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn
python -m pip install catboost
python -m pip install lightgbm
python -m pip install pytorch-tabnet torch

Example
-------
python cesmlc_v6_train_problem_state_model.py ^
  --dataset "C:\\Temp\\cesmlc_v6_seed_akr3aesme01_30d_outputs\\cesmlc_v6_problem_state_training_dataset.csv" ^
  --out-dir "C:\\Temp\\cesmlc_v6_ml_akr3aesme01_30d_outputs" ^
  --model auto ^
  --test-size 0.25 ^
  --train-verbose 25
"""

